metadata.name: Dive ♫
metadata.description:
That, which surrounds me, fills me up.
Calm winds and clear water;
I look up, to breathe in what has been lent to me.  
Then down, to let out everything I believed was my own.

“A reflection of myself, or is it you?”
I extend my hand, and he extends his;
I call to him, and he calls back.
A tear of joy, and I dive in —

I dive in, and there is unity.
I dive in, and there is serenity.

As I delve deeper,
A maze presents itself —
Leading back to where I started, 
Leading back to where I belong.

Dive.
